      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDSTAR HECTOR (6) is a consistent runner who is having his first try here. Comes here a winner after he was prominent throughout and proved too strong to score over 390m at Q Lakeside (22.15). Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Can make it back-to-back wins. GARY INDIANA (4) was quickly into stride and burnt early from the middle draw where he gave a sight, finishing third (23.14) and beaten 4 lengths over 400m at The Gardens. Winning chance. ROBELL DAISY (8) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at Casino over 300m behind Big Cuddle (17.80) in a Grade 5. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Shapes as one to consider. TWO TONE TOMMY (2) did a good job to finish third last time out over 350m at this track (20.52) in a Grade 5, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
